{{TennisEventInfo|1990|Monte Carlo Open|
| date=23 – 29 April
| edition=84th
| surface=Clay / Outdoor
| champs= {{flagicon|URS}} [[Andrei Chesnokov]] <ref name="ms">{{cite web|title=1990 Monte Carlo Men's Singles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/archive/monte-carlo/410/1990/draws?matchType=singles|website=www.atpworldtour.com|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]] (ATP)}}</ref>
| champd= {{flagicon|CSK}} [[Petr Korda]] / {{flagicon|CSK}} [[Tomáš Šmíd]]
}}

The '''1990 Monte Carlo Open''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]]. It was the 84th edition of the [[Monte Carlo Masters|Monte Carlo Open]], and was part of the [[ATP Masters Series|ATP Super 9]] of the [[1990 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Roquebrune-Cap-Martin]], France, near [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]], 23 April through 29 April 1990.

The men's field was headlined by [[Stefan Edberg]] and [[Boris Becker]]. Other top seeds in the field were [[Aaron Krickstein]], [[Jay Berger]], and [[Andrés Gómez]].

==Champions==
===Singles===
{{main|1990 Monte Carlo Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|URS}} '''[[Andrei Chesnokov]]''' defeated {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Thomas Muster]] 7–5, 6–3, 6–3
*It was Andrei Chesnokov's 1st title of the year and his 4th overall. It was his 1st Masters title.

===Doubles===
{{main|1990 Monte Carlo Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|TCH}} '''[[Petr Korda]]''' / {{flagicon|TCH}} '''[[Tomáš Šmíd]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ECU}} [[Andrés Gómez]] / {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Javier Sánchez]] 6–4, 7–6

