The '''APEC Indonesia 2013''' was the 25th annual gathering of [[Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation|APEC]] leaders. It was held in [[Bali]] on 5–7 October 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2013/09/19/indonesian-mps-upset-over-asylum-policy |title= Indonesian MPs upset over asylum policy|author= Darren Mara|date=2013-09-19|accessdate= 2013-09-19|work= sbs.com.au|publisher= [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]]}}</ref> The summit also saw the revival of wearing [[national dress]], which had been explicitly discontinued by US President [[Barack Obama]] two years prior.

==Attendees==
This was the first APEC meeting for [[Prime Minister of Australia|Australian Prime Minister]] [[Tony Abbott]], [[President of the People's Republic of China|Chinese President]] [[Xi Jinping]], [[Prime Minister of Japan|Japanese Prime Minister]] [[Shinzō Abe]] (in his comeback), [[President of the Republic of Korea|South Korean President]] [[Park Geun-hye]] and [[President of Mexico|Mexican President]] [[Enrique Peña Nieto]] since their inaugurations on 18 September 2013, 15 March 2013, 26 December 2012, 25 February 2013 and 1 December 2012, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/oct/04/tony-abbott-miss-barack-obama-apec|title=Tony Abbott to miss out on meeting with Barack Obama at Apec summit|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=October 4, 2013|accessdate=November 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/08/world/asia/asia-pacific-economic-cooperation-summit.html|title=Obama’s Absence Leaves China as Dominant Force at Asia-Pacific Meeting|last1=Perlez|first1=Jane|last2=Cochrane|first2=Joe|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=October 8, 2013|accessdate=November 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/apec-ceo-summit-2013-gathers-government-and-business-leaders-of-the-asia-pacific-to-seek-path-towards-resilience-and-growth-221571371.html|title=APEC CEO Summit 2013 Gathers Government and Business Leaders of the Asia-Pacific to Seek Path "Towards Resilience and Growth"|work=PR Newswire|date=August 28, 2013|accessdate=November 18, 2013}}</ref>

It will also be the last APEC meeting for [[President of Chile|Chilean President]] [[Sebastian Piñera]] (who stepped down on March 11, 2014 following the [[Chilean general election, 2013|2013 Chilean election]]), as well [[Prime Minister of Thailand|Thai Prime Minister]] [[Yingluck Shinawatra]] (who was ousted on May 7, 2014 following the [[2013–14 Thai political crisis|2013–14 political crisis in Thailand]]) and the host, [[President of Indonesia|Indonesian President]] [[Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono]] (who stepped down on October 20, 2014 following the [[Indonesian presidential election, 2014|2014 Indonesian presidential election]]).

[[President of the United States|United States President]] [[Barack Obama]] canceled his trip due to the [[United States federal government shutdown of 2013]], sending Secretary of State [[John Kerry]] in his place.<ref>http://www.aljazeera.com/news/americas/2013/10/obama-cancels-apec-trip-over-us-shutdown-20131042458661862.html</ref>

