{{Infobox government agency | name = Albanian Telegraphic Agency | native_name = Agjencia Telegrafike Shqiptare | type = | logo = Agjencia Telegrafike Shqiptare.svg | logo_width = 125px | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | formed = {{Start date and age|1953}} | jurisdiction = [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] | headquarters = | region_code = AL | chief1_name = Armela Krasniqi | chief1_position = Director General | parent_agency = | website = [http://ata.gov.al Official Website] }} The '''Albanian Telegraphic Agency''' ('''ATA'''; {{sq|Agjencia Telegrafike Shqiptare}}) is the official [[News in Albania|news]] entity of the Albanian government. It publishes news in the following languages: [[Albanian language|Albanian]], [[English language|English]] and [[French language| French]]<ref>[http://ata.gov.al/ Official website] Albanian Telegraphic Agency.</ref>
==History== ATA was established in 1912 following the foundation of the [[Albanian state]].<ref name=bsanna>{{cite web|title=Albanian Telegraphic Agency - ATA |url=http://bsanna-news.ukrinform.ua/bsanna-members.php?lang=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070211065852/http://bsanna-news.ukrinform.ua/bsanna-members.php?lang=en |dead-url=yes |archive-date=11 February 2007 |work=BSANNA |accessdate=23 January 2014 }}</ref> The agency is a member of the Black Sea Association of National News Agencies.<ref name=bsanna/>
