'''Amagoro Constituency''' was a [[Constituencies of Kenya|electoral constituency]] in [[Kenya]]'s former [[Western Province (Kenya)|Western Province]]. It was the only constituency in the now-defunct [[Teso District, Kenya|Teso District]]. [[Sospeter Ojaamong]] represented the constituency for the [[Orange Democratic Movement]] in the [[National Assembly of Kenya|National Assembly]], and did so since 2002.<ref name="afdev">{{cite web|url=http://www.afdevinfo.com/htmlreports/org/org_67094.html|title=Organisation Record: Amagoro Constituency|date=17 April 2008|work=African Development Information|accessdate=13 February 2010}}</ref> In the [[Kenyan general election, 2007|2007 general election]], he was challenged by [[Gabriel Obasie]] of the recently created [[Party of National Unity (Kenya)|Party of National Unity]].<ref name="kbc">{{cite web|url=http://www.kbc.co.ke/story.asp?ID=46476 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071121011940/http://www.kbc.co.ke/story.asp?ID=46476 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=21 November 2007 |title=Seasoned politicians floored in nominations |date=18 November 2007 |work=KBC News |publisher=[[Kenya Broadcasting Corporation]] |accessdate=13 February 2010 }}</ref>
In 2010, the Teso district was eliminated and replaced by [[Busia County]], and the electoral constituency was divided into [[Teso North Constituency]] and [[Teso South Constituency]].
