{{Infobox scientist | name = Annick Willmotte | image = Photo_byers9_001-1cut.gif | birth_date = <!--{{birth date |YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | birth_place = | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | nationality = Belgium | fields = Polar [[microbiology]] | workplaces = [[University of Liège]] | alma_mater = [[University of Liège]] | website = {{Official URL}} }}
'''Annick Wilmotte''' is a Belgian [[Antarctic]] researcher, best known for her research on the diversity and ecology of Antarctic [[Cyanobacteria|cyanobacterial microflora]].<ref name=":0"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.educapoles.org/news/news_detail/the_beldiva_scientific_team_at_princess_elisabeth_station|title=The BELDIVA scientific team at Princess Elisabeth station - News - EducaPoles - International Polar Foundation's educational site|website=www.educapoles.org|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> A genus of Antarctic cyanobateria, called ''Wilmottia'' was named after her in recognition of her work in this field.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://bccm.belspo.be/news/new-genus-wilmottia-honor-our-bccmulc-colleague-annick-wilmotte|title=New genus Wilmottia in honor of our BCCM/ULC colleague Annick Wilmotte|last=|first=|date=|website=bccm.belspo.be|publisher=BCCM Belgian Coordinated Collections of Microorganisms|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Wilmotte completed her MSc (Botanical Sciences) at the [[University of Liège]] in 1982. Her thesis investigated the use of epiphytic marine cyanobacteria as indicators of pollution of Calvi Bay, [[Corsica]], France. She subsequently completed her PhD in Botanical Sciences from the [[University of Liège]]. The title of her thesis was "Contribution to the taxonomic and ecological characterisation of marine epiphytic Oscillatoriaceae (Cyanophyceae) of the experimental cultivation and nucleic acid studies".
==Career and impact== Wilmotte, currently Research Associate of the FRS-FNRS, working at the [[University of Liège]], has recognized research experience in the isolation, cultivation, and characterisation of cyanobacteria by phenotypic and genotypic methods,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Wilmotte|first=A. M. R.|last2=Stam|first2=W. T.|date=1984-01-01|title=Genetic Relationships among Cyanobacterial Strains Originally Designated as ‘Anacystis nidulans’ and Some Other Synechococcus Strains|url=http://mic.microbiologyresearch.org/content/journal/micro/10.1099/00221287-130-10-2737|journal=Microbiology|volume=130|issue=10|pages=2737–2740|doi=10.1099/00221287-130-10-2737}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Wilmotte|first=Annick|last2=Turner|first2=Seán|last3=Van de Peer|first3=Yves|last4=Pace|first4=Norman R.|date=1992-12-01|title=Taxonomic Study of Marine Oscillatoriacean Strains (cyanobacteria) with Narrow Trichomes. Ii. Nucleotide Sequence Analysis of the 16s Ribosomal Rna1|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.0022-3646.1992.00828.x/abstract|journal=Journal of Phycology|language=en|volume=28|issue=6|pages=828–838|doi=10.1111/j.0022-3646.1992.00828.x|issn=1529-8817}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Baurain|first=Denis|last2=Renquin|first2=Laurent|last3=Grubisic|first3=Stana|last4=Scheldeman|first4=Patsy|last5=Belay|first5=Amha|last6=Wilmotte|first6=Annick|date=2002-04-01|title=Remarkable Conservation of Internally Transcribed Spacer Sequences of Arthrospira ("spirulina" ) (cyanophyceae, Cyanobacteria) Strains from Four Continents and of Recent and 30-Year-Old Dried Samples from Africa1|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1529-8817.2002.01010.x/abstract|journal=Journal of Phycology|language=en|volume=38|issue=2|pages=384–393|doi=10.1046/j.1529-8817.2002.01010.x|issn=1529-8817}}</ref> has contributed to the molecular taxonomy of cyanobacteria<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-94-011-0227-8_1|last=Wilmotte|first=Annick|date=1994-01-01|publisher=[[Springer Netherlands]]|isbn=9780792332732|editor-last=Bryant|editor-first=Donald A.|series=Advances in Photosynthesis|pages=1–25|language=en|doi=10.1007/978-94-011-0227-8_1|chapter=Molecular Evolution and Taxonomy of the Cyanobacteria|title=The Molecular Biology of Cyanobacteria}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/9781118960608.cbm00021/abstract|title=Phylogenetic Relationships Among the Cyanobacteria Based on 16S rRNA Sequences|last=Wilmotte|first=Annick|last2=Herdman|first2=Michael|date=2015-01-01|publisher=[[John Wiley & Sons, Ltd]]|isbn=9781118960608|language=en|doi=10.1002/9781118960608.cbm00021/abstract}}</ref> and has highlighted the importance of Antarctic microbial diversity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belspo.be/belspo/organisation/Publ/pub_ostc/sciencecon/41sci_en.pdf|title=Science Connection|last=|first=|date=2013|website=belspo.be|publisher=Federal Science Policy Office|access-date=}}</ref><ref name="rtbf.be">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rtbf.be/video/detail_les-micro-organismes-heros-de-l-antarctique?id=1823662|title=les micro-organismes, héros de l'Antarctique|last=|first=|date=2016|website=rtbf.be|publisher=RTBF Auvio|language=fr-FR|trans-title=Microorganisms, heroes of the Antarctic|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> Her polar work concerns the microscopic and genotypic diversity of cyanobacteria in Antarctic microbial mats (MICROMAT, LAQUAN,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belspo.be/belspo/organisation/publ/pub_ostc/EV/rappEV01_en.pdf,|title=Federaal Wetenschapsbeleid - Politique scientifique fédérale - Belgian Science Policy Office.|website=www.belspo.be|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> AMBIO<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belspo.be/belspo/SSD/science/Reports/AMBIO%20FinalReport%20ML.pdf|title=Antarctic Microbial Biodiversity: the Importance of Geographical and Ecological factors|last=|first=|date=2012|website=belspo.be|publisher=Belgian Science Policy|access-date=}}</ref>) and the use of fossil DNA for cyanobacterial paleodiversity reconstruction (HOLANT).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belspo.be/belspo/ssd/science/Reports/HOLANT_FinRep2011%20ML.pdf|title=Holocene Climate Variability and Ecosystem Changes in the Costal "Holant"|last=|first=|date=2011|website=belspo.be|publisher=Belgian Science Policy|access-date=}}</ref>
Willmotte is coordinating the BELSPO project CCAMBIO<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belspo.be/belspo/ssd/science/projects/CCAMBIO%20EN.pdf|title=Climate Change and Antarctic Microbial Biodiversity|last=|first=|date=2012|website=belspo.be|publisher=Belgian Science Policy|access-date=}}</ref> using high-throughput methodologies to investigate the microbial biodiversity and [[biogeography]] in lacustrine benthic mats at the scale of the Antarctic continent.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pessi|first=Igor Stelmach|last2=Maalouf|first2=Pedro De Carvalho|last3=Laughinghouse|first3=Haywood Dail|last4=Baurain|first4=Denis|last5=Wilmotte|first5=Annick|date=2016-06-01|title=On the use of high-throughput sequencing for the study of cyanobacterial diversity in Antarctic aquatic mats|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/jpy.12399/abstract|journal=Journal of Phycology|language=en|volume=52|issue=3|pages=356–368|doi=10.1111/jpy.12399|pmid=27273529|issn=1529-8817}}</ref> She also was involved in the study of the diversity of [[picoplankton]]ic cyanobacteria in the [[Southern Ocean]] and [[Arctic Sea]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Wilmotte|first=A.|last2=Demonceau|first2=C.|last3=Goffart|first3=A.|last4=Hecq|first4=J. -H.|last5=Demoulin|first5=V.|last6=Crossley|first6=A. C.|date=2002-01-01|title=Molecular and pigment studies of the picophytoplankton in a region of the Southern Ocean (42–54°S, 141–144°E) in March 1998|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0967064502000875|journal=Deep-Sea Research Part II: Topical Studies in Oceanography|series=The Southern Ocean II: Climatic Changes and the Cycle of Carbon|volume=49|issue=16|pages=3351–3363|doi=10.1016/S0967-0645(02)00087-5|bibcode=2002DSRII..49.3351W}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Waleron|first=Małgorzata|last2=Waleron|first2=Krzysztof|last3=Vincent|first3=Warwick F.|last4=Wilmotte|first4=Annick|date=2007-02-01|title=Allochthonous inputs of riverine picocyanobacteria to coastal waters in the Arctic Ocean|url=http://femsec.oxfordjournals.org/content/59/2/356|journal=FEMS Microbiology Ecology|language=en|volume=59|issue=2|pages=356–365|doi=10.1111/j.1574-6941.2006.00236.x|issn=1574-6941|pmid=17132157}}</ref>
Since 2011, she has been the promoter and curator of the BCCM/ULC public collection of cyanobacteria,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bccm.belspo.be/about-us/bccm-ulc|title=BCCM/ULC Cyanobacteria Collection {{!}} BCCM Belgian Coordinated Collections of Microorganisms|website=bccm.belspo.be|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> a dedicated public collection, currently containing one of the largest collections of documented (sub)polar cyanobacteria worldwide. The collection accepts deposits of polar cyanobacteria and allows their distribution to scientists and industries, for further research.
Wilmotte has been the Belgian delegate to the Committee for Environmental Protection at the Consultative Meeting of the [[Antarctic Treaty System|Antarctic Treaty]] since 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ats.aq/devAS/ats_meetings_contacts.aspx?lang=e|title=ATCM / CEP Contact Points|website=www.ats.aq|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> She is also Secretary of the Belgian National Committee on Antarctic Research of the Royal Academy of Belgium<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dev.ulb.ac.be/glaciol/BNCAR/index.htm|title=BNCAR|website=dev.ulb.ac.be|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> and a Belgian delegate to the Standing Scientific Group- Life Sciences of the Scientific Committee on Antarctic Research since 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scar.org/ssg-ls/ls-members|title=Membership|website=www.scar.org|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref>
== Scientific outreach == Wilmotte is recognised for her work in scientific outreach on the Antarctic Treaty<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ulg.ac.be/cms/c_3155716/en/est-on-en-train-de-detruire-l-antarctique|title=Est-on en train de détruire l'Antarctique ?|website=ULg|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://le15ejour.ulg.ac.be/jcms/c_33763/fr/annick-wilmotte|title=Annick Wilmotte|website=le15ejour.ulg.ac.be|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> and also on the importance of Antarctic microorganisms.<ref name="rtbf.be"/>
==Awards and honours== A new cyanobacterial genus (''Wilmottia'') originally described from Antarctica was dedicated to her by colleagues.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fottea.czechphycology.cz/artkey/fot-201101-0007_Taxonomic_revision_of_the_freshwater_cyanobacterium_Phormidium_murrayi_Wilmottia_murrayi.php|title=Taxonomic revision of the freshwater cyanobacterium "Phormidium" murrayi = Wilmottia murrayi|last=|first=|date=2011|website=fottea.czechphycology.cz|publisher=Fottea|access-date=}}</ref> She was awarded the l'Adjudant Lefévre of the Sciences of the Royal Academy of Belgium in 1999.
