[[File:Placki ziemniaczane polish potato pancake and goulash dish 2010.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A potato pancake with spicy goulash (''Placki ziemniaczane z gulaszem na ostro'') served with Bundz ([[sheep's milk]] cheese) and sour cream (perhaps mixed with [[yogurt]]) in a restaurant in [[Zakopane]], Poland]]

'''Bundz''' (also known as '''bunc''' ''([[Podhale]] [[dialect]]'')  is [[Poland|Polish]] [[sheep milk]] [[cheese]]. It is traditionally produced in [[Podhale]]. The drink [[żętyca]] is also produced from the [[whey]] created in bundz production.

==See also==
* [[Bryndza Podhalańska]], a Polish variety of soft cheese made from sheep milk.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:32007R0642:EN:NOT |title=Commission Regulation (EC) No 642/2007 of 11 June 2007 registering a name in the Register of protected designations of origin and protected geographical indications Bryndza Podhalańska (PDO) |author=[[European Commission]] |date=2007-06-11 }}</ref>
* [[Oscypek]], a smoked hard cheese, made in Poland from salted sheep milk

