{{inline|date=June 2014}}
'''Finnish Cultural Foundation''' ({{lang-fi|Suomen Kulttuurirahasto}}) is a private [[Nonprofit organization|nonprofit]] [[Foundation (nonprofit)|foundation]] dedicated to the promotion of [[culture]] and [[science]] in [[Finland]]. The foundation's assets are about 1.1 billion [[euro]]s, which makes it one of the largest private foundations in Europe. Annual [[Grant (money)|grants]] were more than 31 million euros in 2013. 

Finnish Cultural Foundation consists of the main fund and 17 [[Regions of Finland|regional]] funds. It was founded in 1939 to counterbalance Finnish cultural life as the [[Swedish-speaking population of Finland|Swedish-speaking Finns]] received significantly more funding because of their own foundation ''[[Svenska kulturfonden]]''.

== External links ==
*[https://www.skr.fi/en/finnish-cultural-foundation-0 Finnish Cultural Foundation Official Homepage] (English and Finnish)


