{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox airport | name = Matsapha Airport | nativename = | image = Matsapha.JPG | image-width = 250 | caption = The terminal in 2004 | IATA = MTS | ICAO = FDMS | type = Public | owner = | operator = Swaziland Civil Aviation Authority (SWACAA) | city-served = | location = [[Manzini, Swaziland|Manzini]], Swaziland | elevation-f = 2075 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|26|31|44|S|031|18|27|E|region:SZ|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Swaziland | pushpin_label = '''MTS''' | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the airport in Swaziland | website = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 07/25 | r1-length-m = 2600 | r1-length-f = | r1-surface = Asphalt | footnotes = Source: [[DAFIF]]<ref name="WAD">[http://www.worldaerodata.com/wad.cgi?airport=FDMS Airport information for FDMS] from [[DAFIF]] (effective October 2006)</ref> GCM<ref name="GCM">{{GCM|MTS|Matsapha Airport}}</ref> Google Maps<ref>{{cite web |title=Matsapha Airport |url=https://www.google.com/maps/@-26.527038,31.3071493,5058m/data=!3m1!1e3 |website=Google Maps |publisher=Google |accessdate=18 June 2018}}</ref> }}
'''Matsapha Airport''' {{airport codes|MTS|FDMS}} is an airport located near [[Manzini, Manzini District, Swaziland|Manzini]], a city in [[Manzini District]] of [[Swaziland]]. It serves flights of the [[Politics of Swaziland|Swazi Government]] and mercy flights.<ref>[http://www.swacaa.co.sz/airports/matsapha/index.php "Matsapha Airport"]. ''Swaziland Civil Aviation Authority''. Retrieved 13 February 2016.</ref>
Although a new airport for Manzini, [[King Mswati III International Airport]], was inaugurated in March 2014, [[Airlink]] chose to continue flying to Mastapha. However, the Swaziland Civil Aviation Authority (SWACAA) required the airline to end flights to Matsapha on 29 September 2014 and switch to King Mswati III Airport the following day.<ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/201408221546.html "Swaziland: Airlink Forced to Use King's Airport"]. ''allAfrica.com''. 22 August 2014. Retrieved 13 February 2016.</ref>
==Facilities== The airport is at an elevation of {{convert|2075|ft|0}} above [[mean sea level]], the runway elevation is {{convert|2075|ft}}. It has one [[runway]] designated 07/25 with an [[asphalt]] surface measuring {{convert|2600|x|45|m|0}}.<ref name="WAD" />
The Matsapha [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''MS''') is located off the approach threshold of Runway 25. The Matsapha [[VOR-DME]] (Ident: '''VMS''') is located on the field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/VMS/Matsapha_VOR-DME_SZ/|title=Matsapha VOR-DME (VMS) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://skyvector.com/?ll=-26.510,31.334&chart=301&zoom=1|title=SkyVector: Flight Planning / Aeronautical Charts|website=skyvector.com|access-date=2018-08-26}}</ref>
