{{italic title}}
'''''Thebes at War''''' is an early novel by the [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] writer [[Naguib Mahfouz]].<ref>[http://www.complete-review.com/authors/mahfouz.htm Author page at Complete Reviews]</ref> It was originally published in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] in 1944. An [[English language|English]] translation by [[Humphrey Davies]] appeared in 2003. The novel is one of several that Mahfouz wrote at the beginning of his career, with [[Pharaonic Egypt]] as their setting. Others in this series of novels include ''[[Khufu's Wisdom]]'' (1939) and ''[[Rhadopis of Nubia]]'' (1943). All have been translated into English and appeared in one volume under the title ''Three Novels of Ancient Egypt'' ([[Everyman's Library]], 2007).

